01:26:18.034 --> 01:26:20.154
Kind of a generic question for the panel, but if we had to

1485
01:26:20.974 --> 01:26:24.874
go back and look at some of these targets, would you still call them synthetic

1486
01:26:24.934 --> 01:26:28.574
lethal? I guess, an ATR inhibitor or ATM inhibitor,

1487
01:26:29.114 --> 01:26:33.004
just their effect, their broad tox effects or effects on healthy cells,

1488
01:26:33.054 --> 01:26:35.034
are they synthetic lethal, you still think?

1489
01:26:36.094 --> 01:26:36.654
Great question.

1490
01:26:36.774 --> 01:26:40.574
So an ATM inhibitor is pretty well tolerated on its own, less so an

1491
01:26:40.674 --> 01:26:41.494
ATR inhibitor.

1492
01:26:43.074 --> 01:26:43.394
The

1493
01:26:44.454 --> 01:26:48.374
synthetic lethality, I think, has to really be driven

1494
01:26:48.414 --> 01:26:51.724
by a tumor deficiency that gives you a big enough window.

1495
01:26:52.194 --> 01:26:56.174
So you can be talking about the same type of inhibitor, but in different

1496
01:26:56.194 --> 01:27:00.064
tumor backgrounds, you might not have that level of therapeutic

1497
01:27:00.134 --> 01:27:03.894
window than in the other one. So I agree it's not straightforward.

1498
01:27:05.934 --> 01:27:09.094
But I do think there are examples where you might be able to get that synthetic

1499
01:27:09.114 --> 01:27:12.764
lethality. But what we've talked about is that it's not just the starting

1500
01:27:12.854 --> 01:27:13.214
point,

1501
01:27:15.034 --> 01:27:16.694
where you have the potential for a therapeutic window.

1502
01:27:16.914 --> 01:27:19.114
It's then having the pharmacology

1503
01:27:19.954 --> 01:27:23.174
to deliver that in a way that gives you that

1504
01:27:23.774 --> 01:27:27.594
wide therapeutic window as well. So I think the reason we haven't seen other

1505
01:27:27.634 --> 01:27:30.954
examples make it all the way through yet to the clinic is because it's not

1506
01:27:31.014 --> 01:27:32.314
straightforward.

